PRIVACY POLICY

Last updated: March 16, 2026

This Privacy Notice for TheraSessions ("we," "us," or "our") describes how and why we may access, collect, store, use, and/or share ("process") your personal information when you use our services ("Services"), including when you:

Download and use our mobile application TheraSessions, or any other application of ours that links to this Privacy Notice

Use TheraSessions to connect with licensed therapists, book therapy sessions, track mental wellness, and manage your therapy journey

Engage with us in other related ways, including support requests, marketing, or events

Reading this Privacy Notice will help you understand your privacy rights and choices.

If you do not agree with our policies and practices, please do not use our Services.

If you have any questions or concerns, please contact us at support@therasessions.com
.

SUMMARY OF KEY POINTS

This summary highlights key points from our Privacy Notice.

What personal information do we process?

When you use TheraSessions, we may process personal information depending on how you interact with the platform, the choices you make, and the features you use.

Do we process sensitive personal information?

Because TheraSessions is a mental wellness platform, some information you share (such as therapy concerns, mood tracking data, or assessment responses) may be considered sensitive personal information. We only process such information to provide therapy-related services and with your consent.

Do we collect information from third parties?

We generally collect information directly from you. In some cases, we may receive limited information from payment providers or authentication services.

How do we process your information?

We process your information to:

Create and manage your account

Match you with therapists

Schedule and conduct therapy sessions

Provide mood tracking and therapy insights

Communicate with you

Improve the platform

Ensure platform security and prevent fraud

With whom do we share your information?

We may share limited information with:

Therapists you choose to connect with

Payment service providers

Legal authorities when required by law

How do we keep your information safe?

We implement technical and organizational safeguards, including secure servers and encrypted communication, to protect your information.

What are your rights?

Depending on your location, you may have the right to:

Access your data

Correct inaccurate data

Delete your account

Withdraw consent for certain processing

