1. WHAT INFORMATION DO WE COLLECT?
Personal information you disclose to us

We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide when you:

Create a TheraSessions account

Complete your profile

Fill out therapy assessment quizzes

Book therapy sessions

Communicate with therapists

Track mood or therapy progress

Personal information may include:

Name

Email address

Phone number

Passwords

Profile information

Therapy preferences

Therapist preferences (e.g., specialization or gender)

Assessment responses

Mood tracking data

Session history

Communication with therapists

Sensitive Information

Because TheraSessions is a mental wellness platform, users may share sensitive personal information including:

Mental health concerns

Emotional wellbeing data

Therapy goals

Assessment results

This information is processed only to deliver therapy services and improve your experience.

Payment Data

If you book therapy sessions, payment information may be collected by our payment processor.

We do not store full payment card details. Payment processing may be handled by trusted providers such as Paystack or similar services.

Application Data

If you use our mobile application, we may collect:

Device type and operating system

App usage data

Crash reports for debugging

Notification preferences

This information helps us maintain security, troubleshoot issues, and improve our services.

2. HOW DO WE PROCESS YOUR INFORMATION?

We process your personal information to operate and improve TheraSessions.

This includes:

Account Management

Creating and managing user accounts

Authenticating users and securing accounts

Therapist Matching

Analyzing your assessment quiz results

Recommending therapists that match your needs

Therapy Services

Scheduling therapy sessions

Enabling secure video or audio sessions

Facilitating communication between clients and therapists

Platform Features

Providing mood tracking and analytics

Managing therapy goals and progress

Maintaining your personal dashboard

Security and Compliance

Detecting fraud or misuse

Ensuring compliance with legal requirements

3. WHEN AND WITH WHOM DO WE SHARE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION?

We may share your personal information in limited situations.

With Therapists

When you send a session request or book an appointment, relevant information from your profile and assessment may be shared with the therapist.

Payment Processors

Payment information may be processed through secure third-party payment providers.

Legal Requirements

We may disclose information when required by law or to protect rights and safety.

Business Transfers

If TheraSessions undergoes a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.

4. HOW LONG DO WE KEEP YOUR INFORMATION?

We retain your information only as long as necessary to:

Provide our services

Maintain your account

Meet legal or regulatory obligations

If you delete your account, we will delete or anonymize your personal data unless retention is required for legal or security purposes.

5. HOW DO WE KEEP YOUR INFORMATION SAFE?

We implement reasonable technical and organizational safeguards including:

Secure data storage

Encrypted communication

Authentication systems

Access control policies

However, no internet transmission is completely secure. You use our Services at your own risk.

6. DO WE COLLECT INFORMATION FROM MINORS?

TheraSessions is not intended for individuals under 18 years of age.

We do not knowingly collect personal data from minors. If we discover such data, we will delete it promptly.

If you believe we have collected data from a minor, please contact us immediately.

7. WHAT ARE YOUR PRIVACY RIGHTS?

Depending on your location, you may have rights to:

Access the personal data we hold about you

Correct inaccurate information

Request deletion of your data

Withdraw consent for certain processing

Account Management

You may:

Update your account information through your profile settings

Delete your account by contacting support

We may retain limited information where required by law.

8. CONTROLS FOR DO-NOT-TRACK FEATURES

Most web browsers include a Do-Not-Track (DNT) feature.

Currently, there is no consistent industry standard for responding to these signals, so we do not respond to them at this time.

